Loan Default Prediction System
MVP (Minimum Viable Product)
Objective

Develop a web application that predicts whether a loan applicant is likely to default using a machine learning model. The system should allow users to register, submit loan details, receive a prediction, and store the information in the database.

Phase 1: Machine Learning
Goal

Build and train a machine learning model for loan default prediction.

Tasks
Collect and understand the dataset.
Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA).
Clean and preprocess the data.
Handle missing values and encode categorical features.
Split the dataset into training and testing sets.
Train different machine learning models.
Evaluate model performance.
Select the best-performing model.
Save the trained model using joblib.
Deliverables
Clean dataset
Trained ML model
Saved model (model.joblib)
Model evaluation report



Phase 2: Backend (FastAPI + Supabase)
Goal

Develop backend APIs, integrate the machine learning model, and manage database operations.

Tasks
Authentication
User Registration API
User Login API
Prediction
Load the trained ML model
Create Prediction API
Validate user input
Return prediction result
Database (Supabase)
Store user details
Store loan application details
Store prediction results
Retrieve prediction history (optional)
API & Testing
Create REST APIs
API documentation using Swagger
Unit testing for backend APIs
Deliverables
FastAPI backend
Integrated ML model
Supabase database integration
Working APIs
API documentation



Phase 3: Frontend (React)
Goal

Build a user-friendly interface for interacting with the prediction system.

Tasks
Login page
Registration page
Loan application form
Prediction result page
Connect frontend to backend APIs
Form validation
Responsive design
Deliverables
React frontend
API integration
Prediction display